<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870722-0116 </DOCNO><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:Arming Ortega</HL><DD> 07/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LATAM FRESTAEROSPACE (ARO)MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON) </IN><TEXT>   While the U.S. focuses on the Iran-Contra hearings, more Soviet arms flow into Nicaragua. More than $300 million worth of weapons were delivered to the Sandinistas in the first half of this year, according to U.S. intelligence. That's about nine times the direct U.S. military aid provided to the Contras in that period. &quot;The {Soviet} equipment is just pouring in,&quot; one ranking Pentagon official told the AP. &quot;The Nicaraguans are consolidating their military buildup and adding to it everything imaginable.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>